<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="327" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,920,2030]" pageId="10" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,920,946]" pageId="10" pageNumber="327">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1874" box="[321,476,921,946]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,476,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="327">Leptotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of large size, with robust punctuation and microreticulation, close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Coiffait, 1957" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solarii">
<emphasis box="[1324,1340,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="327">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1357,1436,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="327">solarii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Coiffait, H." box="[151,317,960,986]" pageId="10" pageNumber="327" pagination="60 - 81" refId="ref11761" refString="Coiffait, H. (1957) Diagnoses preliminaires de nouveaux Leptotyphlinae (Deuxieme note) (Col. Staphylinidae). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, 24, 60 - 81." type="journal article" year="1957">Coiffait, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but strongly differing from the latter in the shape of the male and female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
